    Excellent
    Really great and affordable way to get around the city. Surprisingly long ride from Dubai Marina to the Burj Khalifa and even further to the Gold Souk, but great value at c.£5 each per day (standard ticket) and c.£10 a day Gold Class. Definitely worth upgrading if you need a seat during busier times. Puts the London Underground and the Paris Metro to shame. Excellent!
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled as a couple
    Written November 6, 2023
  • Deanosaur89
    Edmonton, Canada8,742 contributions
    Connects to the Major Attractions
    We stayed near the red line and found it very convenient to get to where we needed to go and had planned for. There are a variety of ticket options and they cost 6 AED to 8 AED depending on the zone you are traveling too for a single journey. You can get a day pass for 22 AED that covers all zones and the tram line and we used this which we felt saved us a lot of money that would have been spent on Uber. There is a gold card available that costs twice as much and the seats are larger and the car is separate. There is also a separate car for women but my wife had no issues with the regular car until the evening when it was overcrowded but the women car also got pretty packed too. We rarely got a seat but found that the metro was smooth enough to stand on. The metro has plans to expand and hopefully soon as it seems near its limit most of the time for passengers. We were able to get on the first train most of the time but we didn't make it on once due to crowding and recall a few stations where people couldn't get on our train in the evening. The stations were easy to navigate but they could use more ticket machines during peak times. It is important to note that the metro only goes to DXB airport terminal 1 and 3 but there is a free shuttle that can take you to terminal 2. The metro is separate from the Palm Island monorail and that monorail has a pricey ticket. The metro is open until midnight most nights and 1:00 am Friday night.
    Visited November 2023
    Traveled as a couple
    Written November 20, 2023

    Cheap way to get around - but not if you're claustrophobic
    Fast and modern Metro system to see all the major Dubai points of interest. Buying a Nol Card is easy and can be reloaded as needed for fares. Mostly laid out on an East to West route (Red Line) and a SE route (Green Line). Stations are clean and signage is easy to follow. ***Note - the Metro is usually very crowded. Not recommended for people who are claustrophobic because the trains are congested with riders, especially on the Red Line during Rush Hours.

Judee
Livermore, CA1,435 contributions
Clean and inexpensive
Nov 2024 • Solo
I used the metro on 3 different occasions and love it. I watched many YouTube videos and couldn’t figure out what color card I needed for a short visit. It’s the red card for single trips or even round trips.

The first time I went to the booth and had personal help from the attendant who sold me a red card. On my third trip I used the machine and entered the station name that I wanted to exit as per my Google directions and put in cash and received the red card again (with change). You can also pay with a credit card.

Pay attention to the car you enter in. Is it for women and children only, the gold car which costs more or the mixed (men and women) car. Riders exit out the center and the people entering come from each side as the door opens. Not too many seats so be prepared to stand.

It is very clean as there is no eating, drinking, gum chewing or smoking. The price is very inexpensive. I paid 6 AED ($1.63 USD) to ride on one line and then transfer and ride 7 stops on a second line.
Written November 13, 2024

reliable transport
Oct 2024 • Solo
Dubai metro is a reliable and efficient way to cover the often significant distances in Dubai - some 23 km for instance from Burj Khalifa to Palm Jumeirah. There are only two lines, and some landmarks are best reached by taxi from the nearest metro station. Otherwise the metro is clean, fast, reliable and above all very cheap..... and on time. buy the metro card and recharge it whenever needed, it's easy and fast.
